##Special Report: 72 HOURS IN WUHAN BEFORE CITY closure

Hi, Monica and Monica

Function description, here is the "First Finance" magazine (predecessor "first finance weekly") readers club, we discover wonderful business value for you, also invited you to explore the bright business world.

Historically, many deadly viruses have been killed not by humans but by humans living apart from them.

Reporters | Yang Yang Wu, Bingqing Xu, Pingting Liu, Jingmin Zheng, Suyan Guo, Shuxia Deng

Data collation | Yiyue Wang

Charting | Cheng Xing

72 hours after the surge in the number of confirmed cases, the Wuhan COVID-19 PNEUMONIA Epidemic Prevention and Control Command announced at 2 a.m. on January 23,2020, that from 10:00 a.m. on January 23, temporary closure of the city's public transport and air and rail access from Han. It was 23 days since the Wuhan Health and Health Commission first reported 27 cases of pneumonia.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wuhan subway before the city closure. Photograph: People's Daily

The turning point came on the night of January 20th.

That night, President Xi Jinping issued a directive on the outbreak, saying that "the safety and health of the people should be the first priority. ". Later, Zhong Nanshan, the senior Expert Group leader of the National Health Commission, confirmed in an interview that pneumonia in Wuhan could be "transmitted from person to person" rather than "preventable and controllable" as he had previously claimed, and that medical staff had been infected. In fighting the SARS epidemic in 2003, Zhong Nanshan made a deep impression on the Chinese people. His voice exploded on the Internet.

On January 21st pestilence, a strategy game about infectious diseases, topped the paid APP Store list. The game requires players to spread selected pathogens around the globe, creating a super plague that ultimately kills all of humanity. As the pathogen spreads and infects, players can constantly modify its infectivity and resistance in response to counter-measures from governments and scientists.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Pestilence tops paid games list in APP Store.

The game was created in 2012 by London based Independent Game Studio NMIMIC Creations. Barely a week ago, it was little known, but news of COVID-19's pneumonia quickly reunited its players.

Chen Mo, who played the game five years ago, downloaded it again in the early hours of January 21 because of pneumonia in Wuhan, the simulation was based on known information obtained from the news: Difficult mode of selection, source of infection selection virus, mode of transmission selection livestock transmission, symptoms of cough and pneumonia. As a result, it took him a year to wipe out the human race in the game. To sum up his "winning" experience is: "The early strong and weak infectious virus more easily spread, wait until everyone infected to increase its lethality, can quickly win. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Let's hope reality is harder than hard mode.

In its last update in December 2019, the game added a "fake news" feature. Players can spread rumors to fool a subset of the human population, thereby accelerating the spread of disease.

Wuhan pneumonia is certainly not a virtual game in the hands of Chen Mo.. However, in order to overcome the reality of the virus constantly mutating, humans and it is not only a technological race, but also a race in time. Business and corporations are one of the most important forces.

Belated vigilance

On the afternoon of January 21, Cainiao logistics issued nearly 10,000 masks and thousands of sulfur soaps to front-line delivery workers in Wuhan as preventive materials, and required each delivery worker who provided door-to-door service to wear masks.

Later in the day, CTRIP released the news that local hotels and tourism products in Wuhan could be canceled for Free, followed by other OTA platforms such as flying pig and Meituan, as well as hotel companies such as Huazu and Yaduo. Flying pig also added a clause that all medical staff returning to work for emergency treatment of the epidemic can cancel all products booked on the platform free of charge.

In the evening, the Civil Aviation Administration issued a notice requiring airlines to refund passengers who booked flights through Wuhan free of charge. Train passengers arriving or leaving Wuhan before 2400 hours on January 24 will get a free refund.

On Jan. 21, Li Xinxin, who took a high speed train home from Hankou Railway Station for the Spring Festival holiday, saw that nearly everyone at the station was wearing face masks, and that infrared temperature detection devices had been added to the locations where passengers entered and left the station. Four days earlier (January 18) , Yimagazine, a reporter for China Business News, had passed through the station without seeing any temperature measurements, and many people at the station had not realized that they should wear masks, using a common surgical mask, a male student wearing an N95 stood out in the crowd.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Most of the people who travel are wearing masks.

Hankou Railway Station is just a kilometer from the south China Seafood Market in Wuhan, where pneumonia first broke out.

Before Jan. 21, neither the local government nor his company had imposed any restrictions on the movement of local people, a longtime Wuhan employee told Yimagazine. After that, people can leave Wuhan at any time as long as they don't have a fever. He walked the streets of Wuhan that day, saw wearing masks is still a small number of people, coupled with the dense flow of people at the railway station, the sight let him think that the so-called "epidemic" is not serious.

"people thought the epidemic was over at first, but only after reading the official report the day before yesterday (January 20) did they realize the seriousness of the problem, " said Yang Chao, a delivery worker in Wuhan who said the number of people ordering take-out food in the past week had dwindled, even if someone ordered, they would ask for takeout food to be put at the door. "Academician Zhong Nanshan said that those in Wuhan should stay in Wuhan as long as possible. Don't come to Wuhan for nothing important. It's really quite serious. "

A week earlier, Yang Chao had gone to the hospital to deliver food and noticed that all the doctors and nurses were wearing face masks, which he had been surprised to hear was "no human-to-human transmission, under control. ". Now, he received a mask and an anti-viral oral solution from the company. Yang Chao's original plan was to stay in Wuhan to "make money" while many of his colleagues returned home. But that may be about to change. According to Yang Chao, about 90 percent of all restaurants are closed -- as if all but one of the many chain restaurants in Florida were closed.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Box Horse in the Wuhan area of delivery.

Emergency reboot

Until a few days ago, Wuhan had received only limited attention.

With the exception of Hong Kong, China, where the number of suspected cases is rising daily, almost all of the mainland's major cities have gone through busy annual company meetings and booked tickets for Spring Festival outings or reunions back home. Tickets for the high-speed rail line, which is close to the Lunar New Year holiday, nearly sold out a month ago, two weeks after Wuhan Hospital admitted its first suspected case of new pneumonia on Dec. 8. Everyone is planning for the Lunar New Year, which comes a little earlier than usual.

But this week's sudden and intense outbreak has left many companies with businesses tied to it having to respond quickly.

In addition to the first mentioned major travel booking platforms immediately responded to the launch of free unsubscribe information, many of the company's employees have been urgently pulled back to the company overtime.

Late at night on January 21, Cainiao emergency coordination of the deployment of vehicles, overnight a batch of masks loaded into the car, the car, respectively to Wuhan, Beijing, Shanghai and 12 cities of the cat super warehouse.

The programmers of Pinduoduo and Baidu were called back to the company overnight to create a special topic on the prevention and treatment of pneumonia, putting the relevant knowledge and products on a special page. Iqair, a air purifier company, has been actively contacting Wuhan's designated Treatment Hospital since the 21st, offering to donate a batch of air purifier to support key departments of the epidemic, such as fever, suction, emergency and infection departments.

On the afternoon of January 22, Tongji Hospital and Xiehe in Wuhan received equipment donated by IQAir. Rookie logistics also issued a guarantee, claiming that normal distribution during the Spring Festival. None of these initiatives, however, will address the shortage of masks upstream and the logistics of the Spring Festival, which is a special period.

JD.com logistics announced on the evening of January 22 that it had launched a contingency plan to guarantee uninterrupted logistics services in nearly 300 cities and over 1,000 districts and counties across the country during the Spring Festival, starting from today until the 15th day of the first lunar month, priority will be given to orders designated by medical institutions. Honeyville said the current stock could, in principle, cover the supply of masks during the Spring Festival, but that a large proportion of the masks are currently prioritized for supply to Wuhan and first line medical personnel, "The challenges of logistics in the run-up to the Spring Festival are huge. "

The warehouses of mask manufacturers, including IQAir and 3m, have been emptied. Pinduoduo set up a team to find masks, mobilize all buyers nationwide to find mask suppliers. Unlike self-supporting platforms such as jd.com and Taobao, e-commerce platforms such as Doddo, which lack self-supporting systems, rely heavily on merchants to get their products. They found that 3M's big distributors in Linyi, Shandong Province, had the goods, but needs the platform's merchant to pull, therefore the response speed is not quick enough. Doddo and Plan B, which uses Wade, who already has a store on the platform, to push a wave of the brand's surgical masks. On the night of January 21st, the brand had 2,000 units in stock, $19.70 for 20, and was quickly sold out. The second batch of goods sold for 58.9 yuan, Doddo proposed a "ten billion subsidy" program, the platform for this single supplement 40 yuan, has sold a cumulative total of 43,000 units.

ALIBABA received an emergency call from Wuhan at 3:00 a.m. on Jan. 23: N95 level mask, model 1860 or 9132; medical protective clothing above Level 2 and medical goggles above Level 2. It is reported that the current key areas of daily consumption of 2000 sets, estimated 100 days of stock, a total of 200,000 sets.

Companies with operations in Wuhan have also experienced an emergency response in the past 72 hours.

Restaurant and retail companies including mcdonald's, KFC and Hema Xiansheng have told China business news that they will continue to operate during the Lunar New Year holiday, saying they have stepped up disinfection measures at their stores, for example, starting the office temperature process, providing customers with hand sanitizer or hand sanitizer, and requiring delivery workers to wear masks to deliver food. Meituan and ele.me, which are engaged in the delivery service, suspended the delivery service in some hospitals in Wuhan on this basis. The Wuhan Branch of Xiaomi was alerted to the news on January 20, and immediately told its employees to "work from home" from the next day.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wuhan Hema Xiansheng prepared a mask for the customer.

These corporate-level contingencies have all been formulated in the last 72 hours. Many PR companies responded to Yimagazine's interview request on Jan. 22 by catching up with colleagues in the relevant business unit to prepare their corporate communications.

The unknown future

Open or hidden, the treatment of infectious diseases have their own advantages and disadvantages. After the outbreak of Zaire Ebolavirus, Libya declared a state of emergency, imposed curfews, quarantines and travel restrictions, and until this year the country's GDP growth rate remained at 2.5 percent, well below the pre-outbreak rate of 8.7% . Not only have local tourism and food and retail businesses been hit hard, but there has also been a food crisis as large numbers of farmers have fled their homes out of fear of an epidemic.

When viruses display lethal abilities, they are not playing symbiosis or economic games, but zero sum games.

The number of new confirmed cases of pneumonia in Wuhan has expanded rapidly following the speeches by Xi and Zhong Nanshan. Since January 17th, the number of confirmed cases has risen steeply. On the night of January 22nd public opinion turned from an unpredictable number of confirmed cases to scenes of hospital overcrowding and long lines at the hospital gates in Wuhan. Wuhan's mayor had previously announced about 4,300 hospital beds for the city's response to the outbreak. Next, the city will face challenges ranging from health care resources to urban governance.

Photo: CCTV news

Hong Kong, China in 2003 after the SARS incident summed up the impact of the epidemic on urban business: the first was affected by tourism and travel industry; Then there is the struggle for employment, as the outbreak of the virus hit retail, consumer and food service industries, all of which are labor intensive, and the decline in turnover has worsened the employment situation, the SARS outbreak came in the spring, when much of the business of negotiating and ordering goods was disrupted, with the result that trade export figures for the second half of the year were affected.

At 2:00 am on January 23,2020, the COVID-19 announced that from 10:00 am on January 23, the city's bus, subway, ferry and long-distance passenger services would be suspended, citizens should not leave Wuhan. The airport and railway station will be temporarily closed until further notice.

According to Flight Butler data, as of 13:30 on January 22,2020 from January 22 to February 1,2020, Wuhan Tianhe Airport Domestic non-stop flight routes 76,2879 scheduled flights out of Hong Kong; 30 international routes, 293 scheduled flights out of Hong Kong; Four Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan routes, 55 scheduled outbound flights. First Finance learned that some airlines have been informed by the relevant departments to hold an emergency meeting to study the suspension of all wuhan-related flights.

Nor did China's cities during the SARS epidemic in 2003.

(Chen Mo, Li Xinxin and Yang Chao were given pseudonyms at the request of the interviewees. Journalist Trainee Tao Zidong contributed to this report.)
